    "uen": "202131755D",
    "description": "<p>Zijin Mining Group Co. Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as “Zijin” or “the Group”) is a multi-national mining company headquartered in Mainland China and listed on both the Shanghai Stock Exchange (stock ticker number 601899) and Hong Kong Stock Exchange (stock ticker number 2899).</p>\n<p>The Group is principally engaged in the prospecting, exploration, and mining of gold, copper, and other mineral resources with operations in 12 countries.</p>\n<p>Today, Zijin is one of the largest gold, copper and zinc producers in China. Additionally, it generates the best efficacy, controls the largest volume of metal resources reserve, has the largest production volumes and the most competitive performance in the Chinese mining industry. In the Top 500 Enterprises of China released in 2020, Zijin'sefficiency indicator ranked 1st among non-ferrous (gold) mining enterprises. Under the list of Forbes Global 2000, it also ranked 3rd among global listed gold corporations and 7th among global non-ferrous metal corporations.</p>\n<p>Zijin (Singapore) International Mining Pte Ltd is the overseas distribution center of Zijin Group. Its main business activities are trade in minerals, metal ores, non-ferrous metals, gold and black metals.</p>",
